name: Christchurch "OUT OF DEBT" CD
description:
A fifteen track AUS/NZ punk rock compilation CD to raise funds for the earthquake effected people of Christchurch.

Guys like:

Topnovil, The Corps, Kitsch, 5th threat, Dole Day Rage, Foxtrot, Running Bear with Eagle Eye, The Dead Heads, This War.....and a shit load more!

Official fundraiser with 100% of funds made going to The Christchurch Earthquake Appeal.

Let's go!

name: Running Bear with Eagle Eye "She's Ain't Heavy...He's my Mother"
description:
Drunk-rock band Running Bear's debut album released 2010.

Imploding in to the Aus punk rock scene late 2009 with several disastrous shows, before going on to write and record their first album, and play their first international support for Californian Punk rock legends Guttermouth months later.

These boys are a live drunken carny act. Dress ups, banter, and booze fuelled punk with a twist. Not afraid to step out of the square either.... 

Can't wait to see what's coming next!!!

name: RBwEE "Schapelle" Shirt
description:
Inspired by Running Bear with Eagle Eye's classic track "Schapelle".

Shirt also comes in "Pistachio green"

Girls size = M

Boys size = S, M, L, XL

Wear it well!!!

name: Christchurch "OUT OF DEBT" 12"  Vinyl
description:
After the massive success of the "God Save the Queenslanders" punk rock flood-raiser CD release, Pleasant Records have stepped it up and "hand picked" a select few Aussie and Kiwi Punk-Rock acts to take part in Christchurch "OUT OF DEBT", an exclusive 12" Vinyl compilation to raise funds for the earthquake effected people of Christchurch.

With NEW and UNRELEASED tracks from street punkers "Topnovil", to celtic rockers "The Rumjacks", and all the way around to 1980's NZ hardcore legends "Desperate Measures" and "Evasive Action", this is hair product melting proof!!!.... that PUNKS are alive and well and doing what they have always done, TAKE ACTION!!

Track listing:
 1. TOPNOVIL -  Action Boy
 2. THE OPTIONALS - Trade In My Head
 3. THE RABBLE - Burning In the Fire
 4. 5th THREAT - Transmission
 5. EVASIVE ACTION - Militant Takeover
 6. KITSCH - Volunteer_S.P.C.A
 7. CASINO RUMBLERS - Seeing Scars
 8. THE RUMJACKS -  An Irish Pub Song
 9. DESPERATE MEASURES - 1984 (Live)
10. THIS WAR - It Says Here

Official fundraiser for The Christchurch Earthquake Appeal with ALL $20 going to the Earthquake effected people of Christchurch!

Tequila!!!!!
